com.bergerkiller.bukkit.common.collections

Class FilteredCollection<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.bergerkiller.bukkit.common.collections.FilteredCollection<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - - Collection element type
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<E>, java.util.Collection<E>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    FilteredCollectionSelf

    public class FilteredCollection<E>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Collection<E>
    A basic implementation of a Collection that filters some elements from a base Collection. To define the elements to a filter, a Filter is used.

      • createBundleFilter

        public static <T> FilteredCollection<T> createBundleFilter(java.util.Collection<T> base,
                                           Filter<?>... filters)
        Constructs a new Filtered Collection using the base Collection and Filters specified. If any of the Filters filter an element, that element is not exposed.

        The Filter element types can not be checked, so be sure to only use Filters that can accept the element type of the base Collection.

        Parameters:
        base - Collection
        filters - to use to filter elements from the base Collection
        Returns:
        new FilteredCollection instance

      • createBundleFilter

                                           java.util.Collection<Filter<?>> filters)
        Constructs a new Filtered Collection using the base Collection and Filters specified. If any of the Filters filter an element, that element is not exposed.

        Parameters:
